notesStmt.note: Shelomoh: inscribed with his name in a partially illegible Hebrew inscription, undated (1r).
... ben Yosef: inscribed with his name in a partially erased Hebrew inscription, undated (1r).
Manuscript description based on Margoliouth, G.: Catalogue of the Hebrew and Samaritan Manuscripts in the British Museum, London 1965.

msContents.summary: Pentateuch with punctuation, accompanied by masorah magna and masorah parva.

layoutDesc.layout: Columns: 2; ruled lines: 19; written lines: 19; Uniform layout. Ruled with mastara. All books except Leviticus begin a new column. The beginning of a section marked in the margin by an ornamental pen and ink design, with פ in the centre. Each pericope divided into 7 sections numbered with Hebrew letters in the margin. The masorah magna in 1-3 lines in the upper and 2-7 lines in the lower margin.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Yemenite square script of 14th century, with punctuation.

decoDesc.decoNote: Numerous decorated parashah signs, in ink. Masorah magna in micrographical design. Decorated panel for masoretic notes, unfinished, in ink.

binding.p: BM/BL in-house. Spine: 'Pentateuch. Hebrew. Brit. Mus. Oriental 2365.'

history.provenance: Acquisition: Moses Wilhelm Shapira (b. 1830, d. 1884), a antiquities dealer of Jerusalem: purchased by the British Museum from him on 23 July 1881: inscribed on folio ([204v]).
